<paragraph blockId="18.[212,927,1627,1691]" box="[212,333,1627,1651]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1617">
<heading box="[212,333,1627,1651]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="18" pageNumber="1617" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[212,333,1627,1651]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="1617">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[212,927,1627,1691]" box="[212,927,1667,1691]" pageId="18" pageNumber="1617">The name refers to the hair-lined cavity of the hind basitarsus.</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4006358" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4006358" box="[144,1038,705,728]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4006358/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="1618" startId="19.[144,211,705,727]" targetBox="[144,1104,168,674]" targetPageId="19">
<paragraph blockId="19.[144,1038,705,728]" box="[144,1038,705,728]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1618">
Figure 21. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1929" box="[261,444,706,727]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="1618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speiseri">
<emphasis box="[261,444,706,727]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="1618">Megaselia speiseri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
female, Dufour’ s crop mechanism (anterior end to right).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="19.[144,1104,775,934]" box="[144,276,775,798]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1618">
<heading box="[144,276,775,798]" fontSize="10" level="3" pageId="19" pageNumber="1618" reason="5">
<emphasis box="[144,276,775,798]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="1618">Recognition</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[144,1104,775,934]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1618">
In the keys to British species (
<bibRefCitation author="Disney RHL" box="[471,608,814,838]" pageId="19" pageNumber="1618" pagination="1 - 155" refId="ref8043" refString="Disney RHL. 1989. Scuttle Flies - Diptera Phoridae Genus Megaselia. Handbk Ident Br Insects. 10: 1 - 155." type="journal article" year="1989">Disney 1989</bibRefCitation>
) the males run to couplets 130 and 131. This 
<taxonomicName authority="(Meigen)" baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1830" box="[144,362,846,870]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="1618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pusilla">
<emphasis box="[144,255,846,870]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="1618">M. pusilla</emphasis>
(Meigen)
</taxonomicName>
species complex has since been added to (Disney 2011). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Disney &amp; Russell-Smith" authorityYear="2014" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="1618" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="velutinicavus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="1618">M. velutinicavus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is immediately distinguished from the rest of this complex by the internal hairy cavity of the hind basitarsus (
<figureCitation box="[460,587,910,934]" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="20.[212,279,1427,1449]" captionTargetBox="[212,1172,168,1395]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[212,1172,168,1395]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figure 22. Megaselia veluitinicavus male. (A) Left face of hypopygium; (B) tips of right paraphysis and posteroventral region of epandrium; (C) anterior face of hind basitarsus; (D) the internal hairy cavity of the hind basitarsus (anterior focal plane). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4006360" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4006360/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="1618">Figure 22D</figureCitation>
), apart from the hypopygium (
<figureCitation box="[923,1088,910,934]" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="20.[212,279,1427,1449]" captionTargetBox="[212,1172,168,1395]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[212,1172,168,1395]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figure 22. Megaselia veluitinicavus male. (A) Left face of hypopygium; (B) tips of right paraphysis and posteroventral region of epandrium; (C) anterior face of hind basitarsus; (D) the internal hairy cavity of the hind basitarsus (anterior focal plane). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4006360" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4006360/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="1618">Figures 22A–B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
